text: Ishak Pamumbu Lambe (February 6, 1946 â€“ January 1, 2021) was an Indonesian Torajan Christian pastor and politician. He was a Senator in the national Regional Representative Council from 2004 to 2009. Lambe was also the former Chairman of the Toraja Church Synod Worker's Agency from 1992 to 2001.
